# Full deployment guide — step by step

This guide walks you from zero to a **live production setup** that matches how this repo is designed to scale:

- **API (FastAPI)** on **[Render](https://render.com)** using **Docker** (`backend/Dockerfile`)
- **Frontend (Next.js)** on **[Vercel](https://vercel.com)**

You can use the same steps with small changes if your API runs on Railway, Fly.io, or AWS instead — the **environment variable names** stay the same.

**Related (shorter):**

- [render-vercel.md](./render-vercel.md) — condensed Render + Vercel notes  
- [vercel.md](./vercel.md) — both apps on Vercel only (optional)  
- Repo root [`render.yaml`](../render.yaml) — Blueprint for the API service  

---

## What you need before you start

1. **Git repository** with this code pushed to **GitHub**, **GitLab**, or **Bitbucket** (Render and Vercel connect to git).
2. **Accounts:** [Render](https://dashboard.render.com) and [Vercel](https://vercel.com).
3. At least one **LLM key** for production: **`GROQ_API_KEY`** (recommended; used across agents). Optional: **`OPENAI_API_KEY`** for embeddings / fallbacks.
4. (Optional but common) **Google Cloud** project if you use **Google OAuth** — you will create OAuth client IDs bound to your production URLs.

