## Part A — Database and cache (Render)

### Step A1 — Create PostgreSQL

1. Log in to **[Render Dashboard](https://dashboard.render.com)**.
2. Click **New +** → **PostgreSQL**.
3. Choose a **name** (e.g. `eastern-ai-db`), **region**, and **plan**.
4. Wait until the database is **Available**.
5. Copy the **Internal Database URL** (recommended for the API when the API is also on Render).  
   Keep a copy of the **External** URL only if you must run migrations from your laptop.

### Step A2 — Create Redis

1. **New +** → **Redis**.
2. Name it (e.g. `eastern-ai-redis`), pick **region** (ideally same region as Postgres and the API).
3. Copy the **Internal Redis URL**.

### Step A3 — Convert Postgres URL for this app

Render’s connection string usually looks like:

`postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DATABASE`

This project needs **two** variables (see `backend/.env.example`):

| Variable | What to use |
|----------|-------------|
| **`DATABASE_URL`** | Same host/user/password/db, but scheme **`postgresql+asyncpg://`** (not `postgres://` alone). Example: `postgresql+asyncpg://user:pass@dpg-xxxxx-a.oregon-postgres.render.com/eastern_ai` |
| **`SYNC_DATABASE_URL`** | Same credentials with **`postgresql+psycopg2://`** — used for **Alembic** and any sync scripts. |

Replace `postgresql://` at the start if needed; **do not** leak these strings in public tickets or commits.

