## Part C — Deploy the frontend on Vercel

### Step C1 — New project

1. Go to **[Vercel Dashboard](https://vercel.com/dashboard)** → **Add New…** → **Project**.
2. **Import** your git repository.

### Step C2 — Root directory

1. Under **Configure Project**, set **Root Directory** to **`frontend`**.
2. Framework should detect **Next.js** (see [`frontend/package.json`](../frontend/package.json)).
3. **Build command:** default `npm run build` is fine unless you customized it.
4. **Output:** handled by Next.js on Vercel.

### Step C3 — Environment variables (frontend)

In **Environment Variables**, at least:

| Name | Example | Notes |
|------|---------|--------|
| **`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`** | `https://eastern-ai-api.onrender.com` | Render API URL (**no trailing slash**) |
| **`NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL`** | `https://your-project.vercel.app` | Used for redirects / links / OAuth UX |
| **`NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_NAME`** | `Eastern AI Consultant` | Optional |
| **`NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`** | same as backend Google OAuth | If the UI uses Google sign-in |
| **`NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`** | `pk_live_…` | If you enable Stripe |

Use **Production** scope for production keys; optionally duplicate for **Preview** with a staging API URL.

### Step C4 — Deploy

1. **Deploy**.
2. When finished, open the **.vercel.app** URL.

### Step C5 — Redeploy when API URL changes

Any time **`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`** changes, trigger a **new deployment** so the bundle picks up the new value.

