## Part D — Google OAuth (optional)

Only if you use Google login.

### Step D1 — Google Cloud Console

1. [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/) → APIs & Services → **Credentials**.
2. **Create OAuth client** → **Web application**.
3. **Authorized redirect URIs** — add exactly:
   - `https://<RENDER-HOST>/api/v1/auth/google/callback`
4. **Authorized JavaScript origins** — add:
   - `https://<YOUR-VERCEL-APP>.vercel.app`  
   (and production custom domain later)

### Step D2 — Copy IDs

- Paste **Client ID** into Render **`GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`** (and **`NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID`** on Vercel if the SPA needs it).
- Paste **Client secret** only into **`GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET`** on Render (never in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`).

### Step D3 — Match `GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI` on Render

It must equal the redirect URI you registered in Google, character for character (`https`, no typo).

