## Part E — Wire everything together (checklist)

| # | Task | Done |
|---|------|------|
| 1 | Postgres + Redis running on Render | ☐ |
| 2 | `DATABASE_URL` / `SYNC_DATABASE_URL` / `REDIS_URL` set on API | ☐ |
| 3 | `alembic upgrade head` succeeded | ☐ |
| 4 | API `/docs` loads over HTTPS | ☐ |
| 5 | Vercel `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` = Render API base URL | ☐ |
| 6 | Render `CORS_ORIGINS` includes Vercel site origin(s) | ☐ |
| 7 | Frontend redeployed after env changes | ☐ |
| 8 | Google OAuth URLs aligned (if applicable) | ☐ |
| 9 | Strong `SECRET_KEY` / `JWT_SECRET`; no `.env` in git | ☐ |

### Quick verification from the browser

1. Open the **Vercel** site → sign-up or login → confirm network calls hit **`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL`** (browser devtools → Network).
2. If you see **CORS errors**, fix **`CORS_ORIGINS`** on Render (include scheme + host, no path).

