## Troubleshooting

| Symptom | Things to check |
|--------|-------------------|
| Browser **CORS** error | `CORS_ORIGINS` on Render includes exact frontend origin (`https://…`). |
| **502 / deploy failed** | Render logs; Docker build failing (missing env at build rarely needed — usually runtime env). |
| **Database connection refused** | Use **internal** URLs from the API service on Render when both are on Render; VPC/firewall rules. |
| **`alembic` errors** | `SYNC_DATABASE_URL` uses **`postgresql+psycopg2://`**; migrate from a trusted runner. |
| **AI errors** | `GROQ_API_KEY` set; quotas; models in `.env`. |
| **OAuth redirect mismatch** | `GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI` identical to Google Console; HTTPS. |

---

## Security reminders

- Never commit **`backend/.env`** or secrets.
- Rotate **JWT** / **secret** keys and **default seed passwords** before production traffic.
- Use **HTTPS everywhere** (`https://` origins in CORS).

